Privacy Policy – TrackPack.me

Last updated: 08.15.2025

This Privacy Policy describes how TrackPack.me (“we”, “our”, or “us”) collects, uses, and shares information when you use our website.

1. Data Controller

Name: Marco Murgia
Email: mmurgia1307@gmail.com 
Address: Rome, Italy

2. Information We Collect

We may collect the following types of data:

Information you provide voluntarily, such as when contacting us via email.

Usage data, including IP address, browser type, device information, pages visited, and time spent on the site.

Cookies and similar technologies, including third-party cookies from Google AdSense.

3. How We Use Your Information

Your information may be used to:

Provide, operate, and improve our services.

Display personalized or non-personalized advertisements via Google AdSense.

Analyze site usage and improve content.

Comply with legal obligations.

4. Advertising and Google AdSense

We use Google AdSense to display ads. Google, as a third-party vendor, uses cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to our website or other sites.

Google’s use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visit to our site and/or other sites on the Internet.

Users may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting:
https://www.google.com/settings/ads

For more details on how Google uses data, see:
https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites

5. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)

We process personal data based on one or more of the following:

Your consent (e.g., for cookies and ads).

Contractual necessity (to provide requested services).

Legitimate interest (to improve our website and prevent fraud).

Legal obligations.

6. Data Retention

We retain personal data only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described here, unless a longer retention period is required by law.

7. Your Rights (GDPR)

You have the right to:

Access, correct, or delete your personal data.

Withdraw consent at any time.

Object to processing.

Request data portability.

To exercise your rights, contact us at [Your Contact Email].

8. Third-Party Links

Our site may contain links to other websites. We are not responsible for their privacy practices.

9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with the updated date.
